-- MetWest Total Return Fund saw $2.8 bln inflows since Gross news -Morningstar
-- 
-- Tue Oct 07, 2014 04:09PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Oct 7 (Reuters) - The Metropolitan West Total Return Bond Fund had $2.8 billion of inflows since Bill Gross' departure from Pimco on Sept. 26 through Oct. 3, according to Morningstar data on Tuesday.

The mutual-fund tracker also said the BlackRock Strategic Income Opportunities fund saw more than $1 billion of inflows for the same time period.